  Exception: When to Use # type: ignore[ARG002]

  Use type ignore comments when:
  - Public API - Parameter names are part of a documented interface
  - Protocol implementation - Must match exact signature
  - Testing only - Parameter required by test framework but unused

  For SKUEL's internal adapter methods, the underscore prefix is cleaner and more Pythonic.

